		<div id="comment_body_64411092"><p>I recall some rule about questions in news headlines, that if there is a question then the answer is most likely no.  I believe this rule applies here.</p><p>Extreme heat is undoubtedly deadly but even more deadly is cold.  Humans are a tropical species, we tolerate heat much better than cold.  What makes headlines though is that heat often kills quickly with heat stroke and such while cold kills slowly by wearing on the immune system and such so people die of pneumonia or such at relatively random intervals.  Wit<span class="substr"> </span></p></div>
