	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64411252"><p>I will. 250 million is 2.5 x 10^8. 7.6 sextillion is 7.6 x 10^21.</p><p>250 mg is 2.5 x 10^2 * 10^-6 kg = 2.5 x 10^-4 kg. 80 kg is 8 x 10^1 kg.</p><p>The difference in the first case is 21-8 = 13 orders of magnitude. The difference in the second case is 6-1 = 5 orders of magnitude, for a total difference of differences between examples of 13-5 = 8 orders of mangitude.</p><p>Your claim was "50,000 - 100,000 orders of magnitude off". Assuming the "-" is "to", that's 5 x 10^4 to 1 x 10^5 orders of magnitude.</p><p>I think it's safe to say you don't know what "order of magnitude" means.</p></div>
